data.title: Tony Diprose
data.meta_description: Director of Sport and Physical Wellbeing
data.text:
Director of Sport and Physical Wellbeing Tony joined Canford following a career in professional rugby playing for Saracens and then Harlequins where he moved into coaching. In this interview he talks of the importance of enjoyment of sport and the impressive can-do attitude of Canfordians, alongside his view of the highs and lows of competitive sport as crucial learning experience.
